From: Lukas Klizas <lukas@klizas.lt>
Date: Thu, 5 Feb 2026 17:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] brcmfmac: fix suspend failures caused by unresponsive firmware

During suspend, two firmware-dependent paths can stall or fail:

1. brcmf_pcie_pm_enter_D3() sends a D3_INFORM mailbox message to firmware
   and waits 2 seconds for an ACK. If firmware is hung, the timeout returns
   -EIO and aborts the entire system suspend. Fix by proceeding with suspend
   anyway -- on resume, the device is detected as unresponsive (intmask == 0)
   and the existing recovery path does a full remove + re-probe.

2. brcmf_msgbuf_delete_flowring() waits for outstanding_tx to drain before
   checking if the bus is down. During D3 transition, firmware won't process
   pending tx status, causing repeated timeouts across multiple flowrings.
   Fix by checking bus state before and during the wait loop.

Signed-off-by: Lukas Klizas <lukas@klizas.lt>
---
 .../broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/msgbuf.c | 21 +++++++++++++-----
 .../broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/pcie.c   |  6 +++---
 2 files changed, 19 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/msgbuf.c b/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/msgbuf.c
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/msgbuf.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/msgbuf.c
@@ -1410,13 +1410,26 @@ void brcmf_msgbuf_delete_flowring(struct brcmf_pub *drvr, u16 flowid)
 	int err;
 	int retry = BRCMF_MAX_TXSTATUS_WAIT_RETRIES;

+	/* no need to wait or submit if firmware can not be reached */
+	if (drvr->bus_if->state != BRCMF_BUS_UP) {
+		brcmf_dbg(MSGBUF, "bus down, flowring will be removed\n");
+		brcmf_msgbuf_remove_flowring(msgbuf, flowid);
+		return;
+	}
+
 	/* make sure it is not in txflow */
 	brcmf_commonring_lock(commonring_del);
 	flow->rings[flowid]->status = RING_CLOSING;
 	brcmf_commonring_unlock(commonring_del);

-	/* wait for commonring txflow finished */
+	/* wait for commonring txflow finished, but bail if bus goes down */
 	while (retry && atomic_read(&commonring_del->outstanding_tx)) {
+		if (drvr->bus_if->state != BRCMF_BUS_UP) {
+			brcmf_dbg(MSGBUF, "bus went down, aborting wait\n");
+			atomic_set(&commonring_del->outstanding_tx, 0);
+			brcmf_msgbuf_remove_flowring(msgbuf, flowid);
+			return;
+		}
 		usleep_range(5000, 10000);
 		retry--;
 	}
@@ -1425,12 +1438,5 @@ void brcmf_msgbuf_delete_flowring(struct brcmf_pub *drvr, u16 flowid)
 		atomic_set(&commonring_del->outstanding_tx, 0);
 	}

-	/* no need to submit if firmware can not be reached */
-	if (drvr->bus_if->state != BRCMF_BUS_UP) {
-		brcmf_dbg(MSGBUF, "bus down, flowring will be removed\n");
-		brcmf_msgbuf_remove_flowring(msgbuf, flowid);
-		return;
-	}
-
 	commonring = msgbuf->commonrings[BRCMF_H2D_MSGRING_CONTROL_SUBMIT];
 	brcmf_commonring_lock(commonring);

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/pcie.c b/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/pcie.c
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/pcie.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/pcie.c
@@ -2643,12 +2643,12 @@ static int brcmf_pcie_pm_enter_D3(struct device *dev)
 	wait_event_timeout(devinfo->mbdata_resp_wait, devinfo->mbdata_completed,
 			   BRCMF_PCIE_MBDATA_TIMEOUT);
 	if (!devinfo->mbdata_completed) {
 		brcmf_err(bus, "Timeout on response for entering D3 substate\n");
-		brcmf_bus_change_state(bus, BRCMF_BUS_UP);
-		return -EIO;
+		/* Proceed with suspend anyway -- on resume the device will
+		 * be detected as unresponsive and fully re-probed. */
 	}

 	devinfo->state = BRCMFMAC_PCIE_STATE_DOWN;

 	return 0;
 }
